# STL Compliance UI Rule

All NexArr suite product UIs share one dark enterprise SaaS visual language. Pages assemble from shared shell, navigation, card, table, form, badge, modal, and page-header components — not monolithic `App.tsx` blobs.

## Layout (three-zone shell)

1. **Topbar** — dark navy/charcoal; full width of the **main column** (not over the sidebar); includes branding, tenant/user context, and the **ProductSwitcher dropdown**
2. **Left sidebar (AppNav)** — full viewport height (`w-64`); **product workflow routes only** (People, Org, Incidents for StaffArr; etc.); `overflow-y-auto` when tall
3. **Main content** — dark slate workspace; `min-h-0 flex-1 overflow-auto` so content scrolls inside the shell

**Structure (suite + product apps must match):**

```tsx
<div className="flex min-h-screen bg-[#0f172a]">
  <aside className="flex w-64 shrink-0 flex-col min-h-0 overflow-y-auto border-r ... bg-[#0a101c] p-4">
    {/* brand + AppNav workflow links only — no product switcher */}
  </aside>
  <div className="flex min-h-0 min-w-0 flex-1 flex-col">
    <header className="shrink-0 border-b ... bg-[#0a101c] px-6 py-4">
      {/* topbar: product context + ProductSwitcher dropdown + user */}
    </header>
    <main className="min-h-0 flex-1 overflow-auto p-6">{/* <Outlet /> */}</main>
  </div>
</div>
```

Definition of done: no double sidebars, no zero-height main, no full-width topbar sitting above a shortened sidebar column, no horizontal product strip in sidebar or main, content panels use dark theme (not white cards on `#0f172a`). Product app `index.css` must include `@source "../../../packages/shared-ui/src"` so Tailwind emits shell layout utilities.

Must feel like one platform across NexArr, StaffArr, TrainArr, MaintainArr, RoutArr, SupplyArr, and Compliance Core.

## Topbar

- Product name, tenant/workspace context, **ProductSwitcher dropdown** (entitled products only), user/profile controls, global actions
- ProductSwitcher is a compact dropdown — not a row of links or buttons, and **never** a vertical product list in the sidebar
- Dropdown entries: product name + optional short description; selecting launches the product (suite route or direct frontend `/launch` URL via `VITE_*_FRONTEND_BASE` / `buildProductLaunchUrlMap`)
- Calmer than content: no bright borders, loud gradients, or decorative clutter
- Subtle bottom border only; height ~56–64px
- Colors: near-black navy/charcoal bg; soft white/light gray text; muted slate secondary; subtle dark slate borders

## Sidebar (AppNav)

- Same dark family as topbar; **app navigation only** — workflow routes for the current product
- **No product switcher**, no horizontal product strip, no cross-product launch controls in the sidebar
- Group links by **product workflow**, not database table names
- Consistent lucide-react icons; clear active state (brighter bg, left accent bar or soft pill, stronger text, optional accent icon)
- No massive menus, noisy nesting, or per-product styling drift

## Main content

- Dark slate / blue-black page background (not pure black)
- Cards/panels for functional surfaces; strong section spacing
- Card: slightly lighter slate, subtle border, light gray/white text, slate muted text
- Accent blue/cyan or blue-violet — sparingly
- White blocks only for intentional document previews

## Visual tone

Enterprise, operational, calm, dense enough for real work, modern without playful styling.

## Components

| Area | Rules |
|------|--------|
| **Buttons** | Primary = platform accent; secondary = dark neutral; destructive = muted red; consistent radius, padding, hover |
| **Cards** | Rounded corners, subtle borders, soft shadow only when helpful; no glow spam |
| **Tables** | Dense operational data; sticky headers; muted row dividers; clear status badges; no harsh spreadsheet borders |
| **Forms** | Dark-theme inputs; clear labels; obvious but calm validation; consistent required markers |
| **Badges** | Platform-wide colors: green (active/complete/compliant), amber (warning/pending/due soon), red (failed/overdue/blocked), blue (info/scheduled/assigned), gray (inactive/draft/unknown) |

## Cross-product consistency

Same shell, sidebar/topbar behavior, spacing scale, cards, tables, badges, forms, typography, loading/error/empty states. Products differ in nav items and domain terms — not core UI behavior.

## Prohibited

- Monolithic `App.tsx` UI blobs
- Per-product theme systems or unrelated color palettes
- Light-mode-only components or inconsistent shell layouts
- **Horizontal or vertical product lists in the sidebar or main content** (product switching belongs in the topbar dropdown only)
- Platform-admin controls in product UI without NexArr server validation
- Frontend nav that implies permissions the backend does not enforce
- Hidden frontend-only access paths
- Duplicating ownership logic that belongs in product APIs

## Ownership in UI (display only — server enforces)

- **NexArr:** tenant, identity, entitlement, platform access
- **StaffArr:** people, org, permissions, incidents
- **TrainArr:** training, certifications, evaluations
- **MaintainArr:** assets, maintenance, inspections, work orders
- **RoutArr:** dispatch, routing, drivers, trips
- **SupplyArr:** vendors, procurement, parts/materials
- **Compliance Core:** vocabulary, regulatory logic, rule packs, references

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — page owns shell + theme + table inline
export default function App() {
  return (
    <div className="bg-white min-h-screen">
      <header>...</header>
      <table className="border-black">...</table>
    </div>
  );
}

// ✅ GOOD — shared shell + product page content
export function IncidentsPage() {
  return (
    <PageHeader title="Incidents" />
    <Card>
      <DataTable columns={incidentColumns} />
    </Card>
  );
}
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — product switcher in sidebar
<aside>
  <ProductSwitcher />
  <AppNav items={staffNav} />
</aside>

// ✅ GOOD — AppNav in sidebar; ProductSwitcher dropdown in topbar
<aside><AppNav items={staffNav} /></aside>
<header><ProductSwitcher dropdown entitlements={entitlements} /></header>
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — UI grants access
{user.isAdmin && <Link to="/platform-admin">Admin</Link>}

// ✅ GOOD — gate matches server-enforced permission
<PermissionGate permission="nexarr.platform.admin">
  <Link to="/platform-admin">Admin</Link>
</PermissionGate>
```
